# Personal Assistant — gitignore
#
# Rule: NO personal data ever gets committed.
# The repo is the *system* (kernel, plugins, configs, docs). The *contents*
# of the vault stay on the user's local Drive only.

# --- Vault contents (the personal data store) ---
# Ignore everything under vault/ EXCEPT the sample INDEX file we ship as
# a reference for what the auto-generated TOC looks like.
vault/*
!vault/_index/
vault/_index/*
!vault/_index/INDEX.md

# Stage areas — always empty in the repo, populated only at runtime.
vault/_inbox/
vault/_audit/

# --- Per-domain runtime data ---
# These live under vault/<domain>/ which is already covered above, but
# call them out explicitly so the intent is obvious to readers.
vault/journal/
vault/finance/
vault/inventory/
vault/reminder/
vault/fitness/

# --- The user's actual fitness profile ---
# `domains/fitness/profile.template.yaml` (schema) IS tracked.
# `vault/fitness/profile.yaml` (filled-in personal data) is NOT.
# Already covered by `vault/*` above; called out explicitly for clarity.

# --- Secrets ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
secrets/
credentials/
**/anthropic_api_key*
**/telegram_bot_token*

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# --- Virtual environments ---
venv/
.venv/
env/
.env/
ENV/

# --- Testing & coverage ---
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.tox/
.nox/
coverage.xml
*.cover
.hypothesis/

# --- IDE / editor ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# --- launchd run state ---
infra/launchd/*.log
infra/launchd/*.pid
/tmp/personal-assistant.lock

# --- Eval results (large + frequently regenerated) ---
eval/results/
docs/eval-progression.md
